{"nbformat":4,"nbformat_minor":0,"metadata":{"colab":{"provenance":[],"authorship_tag":"ABX9TyMM8pQWAM7WyYChPaPqdRwd"},"kernelspec":{"name":"python3","display_name":"Python 3"},"language_info":{"name":"python"}},"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# Task 1 – Conceptual Answers"],"metadata":{"id":"TOu09ImFh3QA"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["**1. What is the difference between \"Love\" and\n","\"love\" in NLP?**\n","\n","In NLP, \"Love\" and \"love\" are treated as two different tokens because most text processing systems are case-sensitive.\n","\"Love\" may appear at the beginning of a sentence or represent a proper noun, while \"love\" is typically used as a verb or noun.\n","\n","To avoid treating them as separate words, text normalization is applied by converting all text to lowercase. This ensures that both \"Love\" and \"love\" are interpreted as the same token.\n","\n","\n","---\n","\n","\n","\n","**2. What happens if stopwords are not removed?**\n","\n","Stopwords are very common words such as the, is, in, and, of that usually do not carry strong meaning.\n","\n","If stopwords are not removed:\n","\n","The dataset becomes larger and noisier\n","Important words may get less importance in frequency analysis\n","Machine learning models may become slower and less accurate\n","\n","However, stopwords can still be important in certain contexts.\n","\n","\n","---\n","\n","\n","\n","**3.Provide two real-world scenarios where removing stopwords can be harmful.**\n","\n","1. Sentiment Analysis\n","\n","    Sentence:\n","\n","    \"I am not happy\"\n","      \n","    If \"not\" is removed:\n","    \n","    \"I happy\"\n","    \n","    This completely changes the sentiment meaning.\n","\n","2.   Question Answering Systems\n","\n","     Sentence:\n","\n","     \"What is the capital of India?\"\n","\n","     Stopwords like \"what\", \"is\", and \"of\" are important for understanding the question structure.\n","\n","     Removing them can reduce the system's ability to interpret the query correctly.\n","\n","\n","\n","---\n","\n","\n","**4. Explain the difference between stemming and lemmatization.**\n","\n","Stemming and lemmatization are techniques used in NLP to reduce words to\n","their base form.\n","\n","Stemming removes word endings using simple rules and may produce words that are not valid dictionary words.\n","\n","Example: studies → studi\n","\n","Lemmatization converts words to their correct dictionary base form using linguistic analysis.\n","\n","Example: studies → study\n","\n","In short, stemming is faster but less accurate, while lemmatization is slower but more accurate and meaningful.\n","\n","---\n","\n"],"metadata":{"id":"5piAtFX_hnos"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# Task 2 – Advanced Preprocessing Function"],"metadata":{"id":"p0jV9uo3oCGl"}},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":23,"metadata":{"id":"NbA5l7jBgqFt","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774622140836,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":47,"user":{"displayName":"Joharika V","userId":"17828707163987432154"}}},"outputs":[],"source":["import re\n","\n","def preprocess_text(text):\n","\n","    if not isinstance(text, str) or text.strip() == \"\":\n","        return []\n","\n","    # Convert to lowercase\n","    text = text.lower()\n","\n","    # Remove URLs\n","    text = re.sub(r'https?://\\S+|www\\.\\S+', '', text)\n","\n","    # Remove email patterns\n","    text = re.sub(r'\\S+@\\S+', '', text)\n","\n","    # Remove numbers\n","    text = re.sub(r'\\d+', '', text)\n","\n","    # Reduce repeated characters (soooo -> so)\n","    text = re.sub(r'(.)\\1{2,}', r'\\1', text)\n","\n","    # Remove punctuation / special characters\n","    text = re.sub(r'[^a-z\\s]', '', text)\n","\n","    # Remove extra spaces\n","    text = re.sub(r'\\s+', ' ', text).strip()\n","\n","    # Tokenize\n","    tokens = text.split()\n","\n","    # Remove short tokens (≤2) except \"no\" and \"not\"\n","    cleaned_tokens = [\n","        word for word in tokens if len(word) > 2 or word in [\"no\", \"not\"]\n","    ]\n","\n","    return cleaned_tokens"]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["examples = [\n","    \"I have 2 dogs\",\n","    \"This   is   good\",\n","    \"soooo goooood!!!\",\n","    \"WOW!!! This is GREAT!!!\",\n","    \"Visit http://example.com now\"\n","]\n","\n","for text in examples:\n","    tokens = preprocess_text(text)\n","    cleaned_sentence = \" \".join(tokens)\n","\n","    print(\"Original:\", text)\n","    print(\"Cleaned Sentence:\", cleaned_sentence)\n","    print(\"-\" * 40)"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"HkVtoz-eqPai","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774622143342,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":11,"user":{"displayName":"Joharika V","userId":"17828707163987432154"}},"outputId":"50abaab4-2379-4654-ab01-f83fbe5b4062"},"execution_count":24,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Original: I have 2 dogs\n","Cleaned Sentence: have dogs\n","----------------------------------------\n","Original: This   is   good\n","Cleaned Sentence: this good\n","----------------------------------------\n","Original: soooo goooood!!!\n","Cleaned Sentence: god\n","----------------------------------------\n","Original: WOW!!! This is GREAT!!!\n","Cleaned Sentence: wow this great\n","----------------------------------------\n","Original: Visit http://example.com now\n","Cleaned Sentence: visit now\n","----------------------------------------\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# Task 3 – Stress Testing"],"metadata":{"id":"DVh7MJdCoUjZ"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["sentences = [\n","    \"Get 100% FREE access now!!!\",\n","    \"I absolutely looooved this product 😍😍\",\n","    \"Worst service ever... 0/10\",\n","    \"Call me at 9876543210\",\n","    \"This is THE best course!!!\",\n","    \"Visit https://openai.com now!\",\n","    \"Nooooo this is baaad!!!\",\n","    \"OK OK OK I got it\",\n","    \"Win $$$ now!!! Limited offer!!!\",\n","    \"I am not happy with